.TH ETI-RTLSDR-RUST 1 "2026-03-27" "0.3.0" "DAB ETI Generator"
.SH NAME
eti\-rtlsdr\-rust \- receive DAB radio via RTL-SDR and output ETI frames
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eti\-rtlsdr\-rust
.RB [ \-C
.IR channel ]
.RB [ \-G
.IR gain ]
.RB [ \-p
.IR ppm ]
.RB [ \-Q ]
.RB [ \-d
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-D
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-O
.IR file ]
.RB [ \-t
.IR seconds ]
.RB [ \-S ]
.RB [ \-\-device\-index
.IR n ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eti\-rtlsdr\-rust
is a DAB (Digital Audio Broadcasting) to ETI (Ensemble Transport Interface) converter.
It receives DAB signals from an RTL-SDR dongle, demodulates the OFDM signal,
decodes the FIC (Fast Information Channel), and outputs ETI-NI frames
(6144 bytes each) suitable for decoding with
.BR dablin (1)
or similar software.
.PP
The program is a faithful port of
.I eti\-cmdline
(C++) to Rust.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-C ", " \-\-channel " " \fIchannel\fR
DAB channel to tune to. Examples: 5A, 6C, 11C, 12C.
Band III channels (5A\-13F, 174\-240 MHz) and L-Band channels (LA\-LP, 1452\-1478 MHz) are supported.
Default:
.BR 11C .
.TP
.BR \-G ", " \-\-gain " " \fIpercent\fR
Tuner gain as a percentage from 0 to 100. Mapped to the nearest supported gain value of the RTL-SDR hardware.
Default:
.BR 50 .
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-ppm " " \fIppm\fR
Frequency correction in parts per million.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.TP
.BR \-Q ", " \-\-autogain
Enable automatic gain control (AGC). Overrides
.BR \-G .
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-sync\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout in seconds to wait for time synchronization (null symbol detection).
If no DAB signal is found within this time, the program exits with code 1.
Default:
.BR 5 .
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-detect\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Timeout in seconds to wait for ensemble detection (FIC decoding).
Default:
.BR 10 .
.TP
.BR \-O ", " \-\-output " " \fIfile\fR
Output file path. Use
.B \-
for stdout (same as default).
Default: stdout.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-record\-time " " \fIseconds\fR
Recording duration in seconds.
.B \-1
means record indefinitely until interrupted (Ctrl-C).
Default:
.BR \-1 .
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-silent
Silent mode. Suppress status messages on stderr (SNR, FIC quality).
Useful when piping ETI to another program.
.TP
.BI \-\-device\-index " n"
RTL-SDR device index when multiple dongles are connected.
Default:
.BR 0 .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal termination (Ctrl-C or record time reached).
.TP
.B 1
No DAB signal found within sync timeout.
.TP
.B 3
RTL-SDR device initialization failed.
.TP
.B 4
Invalid channel name.
.TP
.B 5
Failed to start RTL-SDR reader.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B Save ETI to a file:
.RS
.nf
eti\-rtlsdr\-rust \-C 6C \-G 20 \-O capture.eti
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Pipe to dablin for live listening:
.RS
.nf
eti\-rtlsdr\-rust \-S \-C 6C \-G 20 | dablin \-s 0xF2F8
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Pipe to dablin_gtk for graphical selection:
.RS
.nf
eti\-rtlsdr\-rust \-S \-C 11C \-G 80 | dablin_gtk
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Record 60 seconds:
.RS
.nf
eti\-rtlsdr\-rust \-C 5A \-G 70 \-t 60 \-O capture.eti
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Replay a captured ETI file:
.RS
.nf
dablin \-s 0xF211 < capture.eti
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Run the automated test:
.RS
.nf
sudo bash test\-capture.sh 6C 20
.fi
.RE
.SH ETI FORMAT
Each ETI-NI frame is exactly 6144 bytes and contains:
.TP
.B SYNC (4 bytes)
Frame synchronization word.
.TP
.B LIDATA
FIC data (96 bytes of FIB) followed by MSC subchannel data.
.TP
.B EOF (4 bytes)
CRC-16 and padding.
.TP
.B TIST (4 bytes)
Timestamp (set to 0xFFFFFFFF).
.TP
.B Padding
Remaining bytes filled with 0x55.
.PP
At 24 frames per second, the ETI bitrate is approximately 1.2 Mbit/s.
